info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 15 at 8:37PM CST until December 16 at 9:00AM CST by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT... ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM CST THURSDAY... * WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory, visibility less than one mile in dense fog. For the High Wind Warning, southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 60 mph expected. * WHERE...Manitowoc, Door, Kewaunee, Shawano, Southern Marinette County and Southern Oconto County Counties. * WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until Midnight CST tonight. For the High Wind Warning, until 9 AM CST Thursday. * IMPACTS...Low visibility could make driving conditions hazardous. Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you. Remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Watch for falling debris and tree limbs. Use caution if you must drive.
